A fire broke out on a ferry sailing from Greece to Italy on Friday with 288 people on board, the Greek coast guard said. The coast guard said it had sent three tugboats and three patrol vessels to help the 237 passengers and 51 crew members off the Euroferry Olympia. There were no immediate reports of deaths or injuries. The ferry caught fire while heading to Italy from the Greek city of Igoumenitsa. The cause of the fire is not known. (With input from agencies)